Photo: ICJapanese authorities have seized a record-breaking 400 kilograms of cocaine worth an estimated $73 million in a bust at a port in the city of Kobe, a customs spokesman said Friday.The discovery in the western city was made last month but came to light on Friday.Officials said that they could not provide additional details because the investigation was ongoing. 
